The paper discusses the development of a safe interaction system for collaborative robots in industrial settings, which involves planning and control algorithms to ensure efficiency and safety during human-robot interactions. This topic falls under the scope of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as well as human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of fast algorithms for real-time computation, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG).
